Forget complex math.

00:04:37.305 --> 00:04:42.135
It's all about concepts and clever
tricks for repo versus reverse repo.

00:04:42.255 --> 00:04:46.155
Think of it this way, repo
is when banks need to receive

00:04:46.155 --> 00:04:48.135
power or money from the RBI.

00:04:48.885 --> 00:04:50.145
Reverse is the opposite.

00:04:50.325 --> 00:04:57.525
The RBI takes money from banks for CRR
versus SLR, remember, CRR is cash with the

00:04:57.525 --> 00:04:59.835
reserve bank, which the bank can't use.

00:05:00.225 --> 00:05:05.775
SLR is self liquid reserves, which the
bank holds itself and for inflation,

00:05:05.895 --> 00:05:07.755
just remember the classic line.

00:05:08.085 --> 00:05:10.365
Too much money chasing too few goods.

