Solving these questions is
a game of understanding.

00:05:17.414 --> 00:05:22.425
For definition questions, just recall
the exact meaning for impact questions,

00:05:22.544 --> 00:05:27.104
understand the terms function, analyze
the change, and trace the consequences.

00:05:27.435 --> 00:05:30.854
For full form questions, well,
you just have to memorize them.

00:05:31.155 --> 00:05:35.385
And for comparison questions quickly
list the key differences in your head.

00:05:37.470 --> 00:05:39.420
Shortcuts and smart techniques.

00:05:39.780 --> 00:05:41.040
Want some pro tips?

00:05:41.340 --> 00:05:43.650
Use contextual clues in the question.

00:05:44.010 --> 00:05:46.170
Always use the elimination strategy.

00:05:46.410 --> 00:05:49.500
Getting rid of obviously
wrong answers is a huge help.

00:05:49.920 --> 00:05:54.120
Focus on keywords and definitions
like overdue for 90 days.

00:05:54.120 --> 00:05:58.710
For an NPA, and remember, many
terms are tools of the RBI.

00:05:59.010 --> 00:06:02.940
If you understand the RBI's goals
like fighting inflation, you'll

00:06:02.940 --> 00:06:05.130
understand why it uses these tools.

00:06:05.510 --> 00:06:09.080
Lastly, a quick scan of
financial news daily will make

00:06:09.080 --> 00:06:10.789
these terms your best friends.

00:06:12.960 --> 00:06:15.120
Common mistakes and misconceptions.

00:06:15.480 --> 00:06:19.320
Now, for the banana peels on
the floor, a common mistake is

00:06:19.320 --> 00:06:21.450
confusing repo and reverse repo.

00:06:21.720 --> 00:06:24.270
Just remember who is giving money to whom.

00:06:24.750 --> 00:06:27.660
Another is mixing up CRR and SLR.

00:06:27.930 --> 00:06:29.310
One is with RBI.

00:06:29.400 --> 00:06:31.260
The other is with the bank itself.

00:06:31.620 --> 00:06:35.340
A big misconception is thinking
deflation is always good.

00:06:35.490 --> 00:06:36.120
It's not.

00:06:36.300 --> 00:06:37.770
It can cripple an economy.

00:06:38.125 --> 00:06:44.155
Also don't forget, the magic number for
an NPA is 90 days, not 60 or one 20.

00:06:44.485 --> 00:06:48.445
And remember, GDP measures
production, not the total wealth

00:06:48.445 --> 00:06:49.630
or happiness of a country.

