00:07:28.364 --> 00:07:30.344
Example, one question.

00:07:30.614 --> 00:07:35.775
What does CRR stand for in the context of
banking and what is its primary purpose?

00:07:36.104 --> 00:07:40.455
A credit rating ratio to assess
the credit worthiness of borrowers.

00:07:40.755 --> 00:07:42.614
B. Cash reserve ratio.

00:07:42.825 --> 00:07:46.190
The percentage of deposits
banks must keep with the RBI.

00:07:46.700 --> 00:07:51.350
C Capital requirement ratio to
ensure banks have sufficient capital

00:07:51.710 --> 00:07:56.060
D, current rate of return, the
profitability of bank investments.

00:07:57.750 --> 00:08:00.660
Understand the question
before moving to explanation.

00:08:00.840 --> 00:08:02.670
All right, let's break it down.

00:08:03.030 --> 00:08:06.420
The question wants the full
form of CRR and its purpose.

00:08:06.780 --> 00:08:11.130
You know, CRR stands for cash
reserve ratio that eliminates

00:08:11.130 --> 00:08:13.590
options A, C, and D right away.

00:08:13.950 --> 00:08:18.720
Its purpose is the percentage of deposits
that banks must keep with the RBI.

00:08:19.080 --> 00:08:21.210
Option B says exactly that.

00:08:21.450 --> 00:08:22.710
It's a perfect match.

00:08:22.950 --> 00:08:24.000
Answer B.

00:08:26.159 --> 00:08:28.020
Example two question.

00:08:28.320 --> 00:08:32.730
If the Reserve Bank of India RBI
increases the repo rate, what is

00:08:32.730 --> 00:08:36.600
the most likely immediate effect on
commercial banks and the economy?

00:08:36.870 --> 00:08:40.350
A commercial banks will find
it cheaper to borrow from RBI

00:08:40.500 --> 00:08:42.150
leading to lower lending rates.

00:08:42.329 --> 00:08:46.290
B. Commercial banks will find it
more expensive to borrow from RBI

00:08:46.439 --> 00:08:48.060
leading to higher lending rates.

00:08:48.300 --> 00:08:51.780
See, commercial banks will
increase their deposits with RBI

00:08:51.930 --> 00:08:53.425
reducing the reverse reper rate.

00:08:53.834 --> 00:08:58.364
D commercial banks will have more
liquidity leading to increased investment.

00:09:00.120 --> 00:09:02.970
Understand the question
before moving to explanation.

00:09:03.209 --> 00:09:05.160
All right, let's dissect this.

00:09:05.490 --> 00:09:09.150
The question asks about the effect
of an increase in the repo rate.

00:09:09.540 --> 00:09:10.680
What is the repo rate?

00:09:11.040 --> 00:09:13.949
It's the rate at which
banks borrow from the RBI.

00:09:14.220 --> 00:09:19.230
So if the rate increases, borrowing from
the RBI becomes more expensive for banks.

00:09:19.925 --> 00:09:21.005
What will banks do?

00:09:21.305 --> 00:09:25.565
They will pass on this higher cost
to us, the customers, by increasing

00:09:25.565 --> 00:09:29.135
their own lending rates, on home
loans, car loans, and so on.

00:09:29.465 --> 00:09:30.815
Now look at the options.

00:09:31.175 --> 00:09:34.625
Option A says, borrowing
becomes cheaper, which is wrong.

00:09:34.895 --> 00:09:38.345
Option B says, borrowing
becomes more expensive, leading

00:09:38.345 --> 00:09:39.545
to higher lending rates.

00:09:39.695 --> 00:09:41.825
This is exactly what we figured out.

00:09:42.155 --> 00:09:45.125
Option C and D are
incorrect and unrelated.

00:09:45.425 --> 00:09:46.265
Answer B.

00:09:48.600 --> 00:09:50.460
Example three question.

00:09:50.730 --> 00:09:54.150
A loan is classified as a
non-performing asset, NPA.

00:09:54.330 --> 00:09:58.290
If the principle or interest payment
remains overdue for a specific

00:09:58.290 --> 00:10:00.180
period, what is this period?

00:10:00.390 --> 00:10:06.090
A 30 days B, 60 days C,
90 days, D one 20 days.

00:10:08.115 --> 00:10:10.965
Understand the question
before moving to explanation.

00:10:11.145 --> 00:10:11.775
All right.

00:10:11.954 --> 00:10:13.995
This one is a direct memory test.

00:10:14.324 --> 00:10:18.855
The question asks for the specific
time after which a loan becomes an NPA.

00:10:19.215 --> 00:10:24.314
The standard definition, a crucial detail
to remember is that a loan turns into an

00:10:24.314 --> 00:10:27.405
NPA if the payment is overdue for 90 days.

00:10:27.555 --> 00:10:30.380
It's a fixed number, so
let's check the options.

00:10:31.225 --> 00:10:34.495
30, 60 and one 20 days are all incorrect.

00:10:34.675 --> 00:10:37.105
The magic number is 90 answer.

